<p>This is a <b>list of writing systems</b> (or <b>scripts</b>), classified according to some common distinguishing features.</p>
<p>The usual name of the script is given first (and <b>bolded</b>); the name of the language(s) in which the script is written follows (in brackets), particularly in the case where the language name differs from the script name. Other informative or qualifying annotations for the script may also be provided.</p>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:502px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Writing_systems_worldwide.png" class="image" title="   Alphabet Latin Cyrillic&amp;Latin Greek Georgian Armenian Logographic+Syllabic Hanzi&#160;(L)&#160;Kana&#160;(2S)+Kanji(L) Hangul(Featural-alphabetic&#160;S)+limited&#160;Hanja(L)   Abjad Arabic&amp;Latin Hebrew Abugida N, S Indic Ethiopic Thaana Canadian Syllabic "><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/9d/Writing_systems_worldwide.png/500px-Writing_systems_worldwide.png" width="500" height="231" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
